### Schedule Job Example - Create a Daily Backup Task
@token = YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

POST http://localhost:8000/api/v1/tasks
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "Daily Database Backup",
  "type": "cron",
  "config": {
    "schedule": "0 2 * * *",
    "timezone": "UTC",
    "command": "backup-database",
    "priority": "high",
    "retries": 3,
    "timeout": 300000
  }
}

### Expected Response
# HTTP/1.1 201 Created
# {
#   "id": "task_xyz789",
#   "name": "Daily Database Backup",
#   "type": "cron",
#   "status": "pending",
#   "config": { ... },
#   "createdAt": "2025-12-16T23:00:00.000Z"
# }

### Get Task Details
@taskId = {{schedule-job.response.body.$.id}}

GET http://localhost:8000/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### List All Tasks
GET http://localhost:8000/api/v1/tasks?status=pending
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get Task Logs
GET http://localhost:8000/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/logs
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Cancel Running Task
PUT http://localhost:8000/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Schedule One-Time Task
POST http://localhost:8000/api/v1/tasks
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "Cleanup Old Logs",
  "type": "once",
  "config": {
    "executeAt": "2026-01-01T00:00:00Z",
    "command": "cleanup-logs",
    "priority": "normal"
  }
}

### Schedule Interval Task (Every 5 Minutes)
POST http://localhost:8000/api/v1/tasks
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "Health Check",
  "type": "interval",
  "config": {
    "interval": 300000,
    "command": "health-check",
    "priority": "high"
  }
}
